table_description: "This table contains definitions of out KPI sets and details of their dimensions ands results, both integer and floating point. Processing sequence and rules for daily to weekly aggregation are also defined."

column.name: KPI_ID
column.description: The unique identifier for this KPI set.

column.name: KPI_NAME
column.description: The business name / title for this KPI set.

column.name: KPI_GROUP_ID
column.description: The identifier of the KPI group that the KPI is a part of.

column.name: KPI_GROUP_NAME
column.description: The KPI group identifier for this KPI set.

column.name: KPI_OWNER
column.description: The KPI group name / business area for this KPI set.

column.name: KPI_DESCRIPTION
column.description: The business description for this KPI set.

column.name: KPI_LEVEL
column.description: The level of this KPI. Lower levels are computed first so higher levels can use their KPI results.

column.name: DIM
column.data_type: ARRAY STRUCT NAME STRING, DETAILS STRING
column.description: An array (struct) of two string values that allow us to understand this KPI dimension.

column.data_type: ARRAY STRUCT NAME STRING, DETAILS STRING
column.description: The name of the dimension we are holding kpi information about
